cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the detection of censorship in social media, specifically microblogs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract features from the communication graph, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely category. The paper also deals with security and privacy issues, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves simulation and modeling techniques, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
